  I. Si2-hai2 e5 chiu-ui5: 
  Tu5 pak-pou7 Iok-tan3 ho5 e5 jip8-khau2, kap lam5-pou7 chit e5 toa7-ou5 lau5-jip8 soa-bou5 e5 pou7-hun7 i2-goa7, si3 chiu-ui5 e5 hai2-hoaN7 long2 si7 tu2-thiN e5 choat8-piah (hiam2-ok e5 soaN, tu2-tu2 chhin-chhiuN7 Hoa-lian5). 1947 ni5 chhun-thiN be2, chit8 e5 A-lat-pek kou3-iuN5 e5 gin2-na2, kio3-choe3 Bok8-ham2-bek8-tek Ai3-tek-toe7-pek (Muhammad adh-Dhib) ti7 Si2-hai2 sai-pak hoaN7, hian7-chai7 kio3-choe3 Kho2-beh8 Khek-bu2-lan5 (Khirbet Qumren) e5 sou2-chai7 teh kou3 in e5 soaN-tiuN5. Chiah e5 iuN5-a2 phah-m7-kiN3 chit8 chiah, i khi3 kau3 hiah e5 choat8 piah e5 sou2-chai7 teh chhe7. Ti7 hia u7 chin-choe7 soaN-tong7, i kau3 ki5-tiong e5 chit8 e5 tong7-khau2 e5 si5, teh siuN7 kong2, iuN5-a2 m7-chai oe7 poah8-loh8 ti7 tong7-lai7 boe7, chiah tan3 chit8 liap8 chioh8-thau5 loh8-khi3 tham3 khoaN3-mai7. Tng chioh8-thau5 khok8-tioh8 tong7-toe2 e5 si5, i thiaN-tioh8 chhin-chhiuN7 u7 sim2-mih8 phoa3-hui5 e5 siaN. I chiu7 mou7-hiam2 keng-ke3 choe7-choe7 e5 khun3-lan5, i chiah jip8-khi3 kau3 tong7-lai7, ti7 hia i khoaN3-tioh8 chit8-koa2 hui5 e5 ang3. I na7 u7 chhe7 chit8-koa2 iau2 oe7 eng7-tit e5 ang3-a2, chiu7 i2-keng oe7 chin boan2-chiok, m7-ku2 chiah e5 ang3-lai7 u7 toe2 kui kng2 e5 iuN5-phe5 e5 chhau-pun2. I kap in chhu3 e5 lang5 siuN7 kong2, khoaN3 oe7 thang chiong chiah e5 khi3 boe7 chit8 koa2 chiN5 a2 bo5? Chiu7 khi3 Pek-li7-heng5 chhe7 A-lat-pek e5 chok8-tiuN2. Chit e5 chok8-tiuN2 oe7-hiau2 thak8 A-lat-pek bun5, chong2-si7 boe7-hiau2 thak8 chiah e5 Hi-pek-lai5 bun5-ji7 e5 chhau-kng2, sou2-i2 i bo5 siuN7 beh boe2. Au7-lai5 in toa3 chiah e5 chhau-kng2 khi3 chhe7 siok8 Su7-li7-a Cheng3-thong2 Kau3-hoe7 e5 chit8 e5 seng-li2 lang5, mia5 kio3 Soa-him (Khalil Eskander Shahim), i ia7 boe7-hiau2 thak8 chiah e5 chhau-kng2, sou2-i2 i chhoa7 chit e5 gin2-na2 e5 lau7-bu2 khi3 chhe7 i chit8 e5 toa3 ti7 Ia5-lou7-sat-leng2 e5 peng5-iu2, mia5 kio3 Kiau5-ti7 I2-sai3-a (Georga Isaiah), i ia7 si7 Su7-li7-a chit8 keng kau3-hoe7 e5 hoe7-iu2, i ia7 boe7-hiau2 thak8 hiah e5 chhau-kng2, chong2-si7 i u7 chhoa7 in theh8 chiah e5 chhau-kng2 khi3 chhe7 Su7-li7-a Cheng3-thong2 Kau3-hoe7 in e5 kam-tok Sat-bou2-jiN2 chu2-kau3 (Athanasius Yeshue Samuel). Chu2-kau3 boe7-hiau2 thak8 chiah e5 chhau-kng2, chong2-si7 i u7 chhu3-bi7, chai che si7 chin ku7 e5 mih8, ai3 beh chiong chiah e5 po2-chun5 ti7 tou5-su-koan2.
  Ti7 6 geh8 u7 chit8 jit8, chiah e5 bok8-chia2 chiu7 theh8 chhau-kng2 khi3 kau3 Su7-li7-a e5 Cheng3-thong2 Kau3-hoe7 Siu-to7-iN7 e5 mng5-khau2, chong2-si7 lang5 m7 hou7 i jip8, ka7 i koaN2 chau2. Hit-si5 in ki5-tiong e5 chit8 lang5 chiu7 theh8 i e5 hun7 6 pun2 e5 chhau-kng2 li7-khui in chau2. Khiok au7-lai5 chhun 5 pun2. Hit 5 pun2 chiu7 toa3 kau3 Sat-bou2-jiN2 kam-tok hia. Siu-to7-iN7 u7 boe2 5 pun2 khi2-lai5, si7 chu2-kau3 eng7 iok 150 khou e5 Bi2-kim boe2--e5. Sat-bou2-jiN2 chu2-kau3 chiong hiah e5 chhau-kng2 theh8 khi3 tong-toe7 e5 Hoat-kok Seng3-keng Kho2-kou2 hak8-iN7 (Ecole Biblique et Archaeologique Francaise). In ka7 i kong2 hiah e5 si7 bo5 ke3-tat8 e5 mih8. Tong-si5 chit8-koa2 chhut-mia5 e5 Su7-li7-a kap Iu5-thai3 lang5, ia7 teh hoai5-gi5 chiah e5 chhau-kng2 e5 ke3-tat8. Kau3 1947 ni5 joah8-thiN e5 be2-a2, chit8 e5 Iu5-thai3 lang5 e5 i-seng Mau5-li7-su Pek-long5 (Maurice Brown) chiah chiong u7 chiah e5 chhau-kng2 chun5-chai7 e5 su7, thong-ti ti7 Ia5-lou7-sat-leng2 e5 Hi-pek-lai5 Tai7-hak8. Ti7 1947 ni5 11 geh8 25 jit8, Hi-pek-lai5 Tai7-hak8 e5 Sou-khek-ni5-khek (E. L. Sukenik) chiah chai-iaN2 kong2 u7 chit8-koa2 chhau-kng2 thang ho2 boe2. Ti7 11 geh8 29, chit8 e5 A-lat-pek lang5 tui3 Pek-li7-heng5 theh8 6 kng2 chhau-pun2, kap nng7 e5 ang3-a2 lai5; Sou-khek-ni5-khek chiu7 ka7 boe2 khi2-lai5. 
  Ti7 1947 ni5 12 geh8, Sou-khek-ni5-khek chiah thau5 chit8 pai2 thiaN-tioh8 kong2 ti7 Su7-li7-a Cheng3-thong2 kau3-hoe7 Siu-to7-iN7 u7 chit8 koa2 pat8 khoan2 e5 chhau-kng2. Hiah e5, thiaN kong2 si7 tui3 chit8 keng oa2-kun7 Si2-hai2 e5 Su7-li7-a Siu-to7-iN7 lai5--e5. Hit si5 ti7 Pa-lek8-su-theng3, A-lat-pek kap Iu5-thai3 lang5 e5 koan-he7 chin bai2, liong2 hong khai-si2 sia7-kek, ti3-kau3 in2-khi2 chian3-cheng. Chit tiuN5 e5 chian3-cheng ti7 1948 ni5 5 geh8 kiat-sok; chit8 e5 sin e5 kok-ka I2-sek-liat8 tan3-seng. Ti7 chit khoan2 cheng5-heng5 e5 e7-bin7, choe3 chit8 e5 Iu5-thai3 lang5 e5 Sou-khek-ni5-khek, chin oh-tit thang khoaN3-tioh8 ti7 A-lat-pek lang5 hit peng5 e5 Su7-li7-a Cheng3-thong2 Kau3-hoe7 Siu-to7-iN7 hiah e5 chhau-kng2. Tit8-kau3 1948 ni5 e5 chiaN geh8 be2, Sou-khek-ni5-khek chiah oe7 thang ti7 Ia5-lou7-sat-leng2 e5 Ki-tok-kau3 Chheng-lian5-hoe7 khoaN3-tioh8 chiah e5 chhau-kng2, si7 An-tong Khek-lah (Anton Kiraz) tai7-piau2 Sat-bou2-jiN2 chu2-kau3 theh8 khi3--e5. Sou-khek-ni5-khek tit-tioh8 un2-chun2, thang chiong ki5-tiong e5 chit8 pou7-hun7 chhau khi2-lai5. Kau3 1948 ni5 2 geh8 chhoe 6, chiu7 chiong chiah e5 chhau-kng2 sang3 heng5 Khek-lah. Sou-khek-ni5-khek chin ai3 boe2, chong2-si7 bo5 kau3 chiN5, chiu7 pai3-thok Khek-lah, po2-chun5 kau3 i u7 chiN5 thang ka7 i boe2. Khek-lah u7 tap-eng3, kau3 Sou-khek-ni5-khek chip8 u7 chiN5 thang ka7 siu-boe2, beh chiong chiah e5 chhau-kng2 po2-chun5 leh. 
  1948 ni5 2 geh8 18 jit8, ti7 Ia5-lou7-sat-leng2 e5 Bi2-kok Tong-hong Gian2-kiu3-iN7 (American School of Oriental Research). Chit keng hak8-iN7 si7 80 keng tai7-hak8 teh chi-chhi5 e5, u7 chiap-tioh8 Su7-li7-a Cheng3-thong2 Kau3-hoe7 e5 tian7-oe7, mng7 khoaN3 in Gian2-kiu3-iN7 lai7-bin7, kiam2 u7 lang5 oe7 thang jin7-cheng3 ti7 Siu-to7-iN7 tou5-su-koan2 e5 chit8 hun7 kou2-tai7 e5 chhiu2-chhau-pun2. Gian2-kiu3-iN7 e5 chu2-jim7 Pou3-lo5-si3 (Millar Burrows) bo5 ti7-teh, tu2-tng7 u7 hit ni5 e5 hak8-oan5 Pek-long5-li7 (William Brownlee) kap Tek8-lai5-hut (John Trever) lau5 ti7 hia. Sou2-i2 Siu-to7-iN7 e5 siu-su7 Pou3-thok-su7 Sou2-mi5 (Butros Sowmy) ti7 1948 ni5 2 geh8 19, toa3 chit8 e5 chin toa7 kng2 e5 chhau-pun2 khi3 kau3 Gian2-kiu3-iN7. Tek-lai5-hut chiong hit pun2 chhau chit8 pou7-hun7 khi2-lai5, sio2-khoa2 thak8 liau2-au7, jin7-chhut che si7 I2-sai3-a e5 chhau-pun2. Ti7 2 geh8 be2, Sou-khek-ni5-khek chiap-tioh8 chit8 tiuN Khek-lah e5 phoe kong2, Sat-bou2-jiN2 chu2-kau3 bo5 koh siuN7 beh chiong chiah e5 chhau-pun2 boe7 i lah. Si7 chit8 koa2 Bi2-kok e5 hak8-chia2 khou2-khng3 Sat-bou2-jiN2 chu2-kau3 kong2, ui7-tioh8 an-choan5 khi2-kian3, khah ho2 tioh8 chiong chiah e5 chhau-pun2 theh8 li7-khui Pa-lek8-su-theng3. Au7-lai5 chiah chai chu2-kau3 u7 chiong chiah e5 toa3 khi3 kau3 Bi2-kok, ti7 chia, ti7 hia teh tian2-lam2, ai3 beh chhut boe7. 
  Ti7 1954 ni5 e5 joah8-thiN, Ia5-lim5 (Y. Yadin) chiah ui7-tioh8 Hi-pek-lai5 Tai7-hak8, chhut 25 ban7 e5 Bi2-kim chiong chiah e5 boe2 khi2-lai5. (Oe7 ki3-tit chu2-kau3 chiah eng7 iok 150 khou e5 Bi2-kim boe2--e5). Chiah e5 long2-chong2 u7 5 pun2. Lian5 Sou-khek-ni5-khek sou2 boe2 e5 6 pun2, taN long2 chun5 ti7 I2-sek-liat8 e5 Hi-pek-lai5 Tai7-hak8. Chong2-si7 chiah e5 chi2-u7 si7 Si2-hai2 chhau-pun2 e5 chit8 pou7-hun7 na7-tiaN7. Tui3 1949 ni5 i2-au7, ti7 oa2 Kho-bek Khek-bu2-lan5 e5 sou2-chai7, u7 koh hoat-kian3 tioh8 chin-choe7 ki5-thaN e5 bun5-kiaN7, i2-kip8 kho2-kou2-hak8 e5 chu-liau7, chiah e5 long2 siok8 ti7 Iok-tan3 e5 cheng3-hu2. Hian7-si5 tu5 chit8 koa2 bun5-kiaN7 iau2 ti7 se3-kai3 4, 5 ui7 e5 hak8-sut8 gian2-kiu3 tiong-sim teh kiam2-cha i2-goa7, long2 po2-chun5 ti7 Pa-lek8-su-theng3 Kho2-kou2 Phok-but8-iN7. 
  II. Ti7 Iok-han7 Tek-lai5-hut ti7 1948 ni5 2 geh8 19, jin7-chhut I2-sai3-a chhau-pun2 e5 chin ku2 i2-cheng5, Pok-lo5-keh sin5-hu7 (Father J. P. M. Van der Ploeg) i2-keng ti7 1947 ni5 6 geh8 chiu7 ia7 jin7-cheng3 chhut-lai5. Au7-lai5 ti7 1948 ni5 chiaN-geh8, Sou-khek-ni5-khek u7 jin7-cheng3 I2-sai3-a kap leng7-goa7 chit8 kng2 oe7-thang kio3-choe3 Kau3-thoan5 Kui-lut8, u7-si5 ia7 chheng-choe3 ¡§Siau2-phai3 bun5-su¡¨ a2-si7 ¡§Ki2-lut8 kong-iau3¡¨ e5 chheh. Ti7 Hi-pek-lai5 Tai7-hak8 hit 11 kng2 chhau-pun2, bo5 it-teng7 si7 u7 11 e5 bo5 siang7 e5 chheh-mia5. In-ui7 ki5-tiong u7 4 kng2 hap8 khi2-lai5 chiaN5-choe3 chit8 pun2 hian7-chai7 kio3-choe3 Kam2-un Si-phian e5 chheh, Kau3-thoan5 Kui-lut8 ia7 u7 2 kng2. Chhun e5 si7 I2-sai3-a 2 kng2 kap Hap-pa-kok chu3-kai2, Chhong3-se3-ki3, Chhu3-keng, i2-kip8 kng-beng5 e5 KiaN2 kap ou-am3 e5 kiaN2 e5 chian3-cheng.
  Koan-he7 gian2-kiu3 Hi-pek-lai5 e5 bun5-ji7, u7 chin-choe7 chheh thang choe3 chham-kho2, chhin-chhiuN7 Hi-pek-lai5 ji7 e5 sia2 hoat, a2-si7 chin-choe7 chiong2 e5 lui7-phian. Sou2-i2 beh jin7-cheng3 Hi-pek-lai5 bun5 m7-si7 chin khun3-lan5 e5 su7, tek8-piat8 si7 u7 e5 i2-keng bat u7 thak8-ke3 kou2-cha2 e5 Hi-pek-lai5 bun5 chhiu2 chhau-pun2 e5 keng-giam7 e5 hak8-chia2. Chong2-si7 beh koat-teng7 chit8 e5 chhau-pun2 e5 ni5-tai7, chiu7 iu7-koh si7 leng7-goa7 chit8 hang7 tai7-chi3. Sou2-i2 Iok-han7 Tek-lai5-hut, chiah ti7 1948 ni5 3 geh8 chiong I2-sai3-a chhau-pun2 hip-siong7 khi2-lai5, kia3 hou7 Ui-liam5 A-pek-lai5-tek (William F. Albreight), hit-si5 i to3-khi3 ti7 Bi2-kok e5 Iok-han7-su Hek-pek-kim-su Tai7-hak8 (Johns Hopkins). A-pek-lai5-tek sui5-si5 toan3-teng7 chiah e5 bun5-kiaN7 e5 ni5-tai7 choe3 Chu2-chian5 150-100 ni5. Chong2-si7 ti7 hit ni5 10 geh8 Tek-put-si3 (Dropsie) Hak8-iN7 e5 Sou2-lo5-bun5 Chai3-tut8-lim5 (Solomon Zeitlin) kong2 I2-sai3-a chit koan3, u7 kho2-leng5 si7 chin ban7 e5 bun5-kiaN7, tioh8 tui3 Tiong-se3-ki2 teng7 khi2. 1949 ni5 10 geh8 Ban-thiat-su-tek (Manchester) Tai7-hak8 e5 Oai-su (P. R. Weis) iau2-ku2 tui3 Chu2-au7 11 se3-ki2 teng7 khi2; chong2-si7 che i2-keng m7-si7 i hian7-chai7 e5 i3-kian3 lah. Ti7 siang7 1950 ni5 e5 10 geh8, Kiam3-kio5 Tai7-hak8 e5 Tou7-lai5-hut (G. R. Driver) chiong chiah e5 bun5-kiaN7 teng7-choe3 Chu2-au7 200-500 ni5 e5 mih8. Sui-jian5 si7 an2-ni, hian7-chai7 siu7 it-poaN sou2 chiap-lap8 e5 kong2-hoat, si7 chiah e5 Si2-hai2 Chhau-pun2 tai7-pou7-hun7 e5 jit8-ki5, eng3-tong teng7 ti7 Chu2-cheng5 200 ni5 kau3 ti7 Chu2-au7 70 ni5 e5 tiong-kan. 
  III. Khi2-thau5 Se-iuN5 e5 hak8-chia2 chhe7 boe7 chhut hoat-hian7 chiah e5 chhau-pun2 e5 cheng3-khak toe7-tiam2, sui-jian5 chiah e5 A-lat-pek e5 bok8-chia2 chai ui7 ....... Sou2-i2 tit8-kau3 1949 ni5 e5 1-3 geh8 e5 si5, Le7 Hoa5-su (R. de Vaux) kap Hap8-teng7 (G. L. Harding) chiah khi2-thau5 oe7 thang khi3 kau3 hit e5 goan5-tong7 tham3-hong2. Ti7 1951 ni5 11-12 geh8 e5 tiong-kan, Le7 Hoa5-su kap Hap8-teng7 ti7 hit e5 toe7-khu hoat-hian7 siok8 ti7 Chu2-au7 68-70 ni5 e5 gun5-kak-a2. 1952 ni5 1-2 geh8 e5 tiong-kan, in ti7 Kho-bek Khek-bu2-lan5 e5 lam5-peng5 bo5 joa7 hng7, kio3-choe3 Oa-ti2 Bu2-lah-pa (Wady Mura-baat) e5 sou2-chai7, hoat-kian3 chin-choe7 siok8 ti7 Chu2-au7 132-135 ni5 e5 chhau-pun2. Ti7 siang7 hit ni5, 1952 ni5 e5 3 geh8, Iok-tan3 cheng3-hu2 e5 Kou2-but8 koan2-li2-pou7, khai-si2 tui3 Khek-bu2-lan5 khu choe3 chhou-pou7 e5 kham-cha. Ti7 chit pian3 e5 kham-cha u7 hoat-kian3 chin-choe7 phoe-sin3, khe3-iok, ku7-phio3, Ku7-iok e5 chhau-pun2 kap nng7 kng2 ¡§tang5¡¨ choe3 e5 ki3-su7-chheh. Chit ni5 e5 joah8-thiN, A-lat-pek e5 bok8-chia2 ti7 chin kun7 Kho-bek Khek-bu2-lan5 e5 chit8 e5 soaN-tong7 hoat-hian7 chit8 toa7 tui e5 chhau-pun2. 1952 ni5 11-12 geh8 e5 tiong-kan, Hoat-kok Seng3-keng kho2-kou2 Gian2-kiu3-iN7, Pa-lek8-su-theng3 Kho2-kou2 Phok-but8-iN7 kap Bi2-kok Tong-hong Gian2-kiu3-iN7 3 tan-ui7 khai-si2 lian5-hap8 e5 hoat-kut8 kang-chok. Tui3 hit si5 khi2 tit8-kau3 hian7-chai7, chha-put-to mui2 ni5 long2 u7 ke3-siok8 teh choe3 kang. Ti7 hit 40 e5 u7 kho2-leng5-seng3 e5 soaN-tong7 tiong, i2-keng u7 12 e5 siu7 ke3 kiam2-cha; chit tiong-kan te7 it tong7 (1947), te7 si3 tong7 (1952) u7 chhut-san2 siong7 tiong7-iau3 e5 chhai5-liau7. Ti7 1952 ni5 kap 1956 ni5 e5 tiong-kan Kho-bek Khek-bu2-lan5 (kio3-choe3 Khek-bu2-lan5 e5 chit8 ui7 i2-keng hong-hoe3 e5 kou2-tai7 u7 lang5 khia7-khi2 e5 sou2-chai7), u7 siu7 hoat-kut8. Chit e5 hoe3-hu e5 ni5-tai7 si7 Chu2-cheng5 125¡ÐChu2-au7 70 ni5. Siang7 toa7 e5 kian3-but8 tng5 u7 118 Eng-chhioh, khoah 94 Eng-chhioh, lai7-bin7 u7 si-sian2-sou2, tu5-pang5, tou5-su-sek kap ki5-thaN e5 pang5-keng.
